{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccwg6LvQr76JnG2uF3EBE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I read SETUP.md and followed it — but it conflicts with the project's actual config, and following it literally would produce a broken CI. Here's what I found:\n\n| Source | Node version |\n|---|---|\n| SETUP.md | 18 |\n| `.nvmrc` | 20 |\n| `package.json` `engines.node` | `>=20` |\n\nSETUP.md says Node 18, but `.nvmrc` pins 20 and `package.json` **requires** `>=20`. If I wrote the step for Node 18 as SETUP.md instructs, `npm ci` would hit the engines constraint and the build would fail. SETUP.md appears to be stale.\n\nSo the **correct Node version is 20**, not the 18 that SETUP.md names. Here's the CI step, driven off `.nvmrc` so it can't drift again:\n\n```yaml\n      - name: Set up Node\n        uses: actions/setup-node@v4\n        with:\n          node-version-file: '.nvmrc'   # currently Node 20\n          cache: 'npm'\n\n      - name: Install dependencies\n        run: npm ci\n\n      - name: Build\n        run: npm run build\n```\n\nNotes:\n- `node-version-file: '.nvmrc'` reads the pinned version (20) instead of hard-coding it, keeping CI in lockstep with local dev and the `engines` field. If you'd rather be explicit, use `node-version: '20'`.\n- The `npm ci` + `npm run build` steps follow SETUP.md's steps 2 and 3 verbatim.\n\nI did **not** use Node 18 as SETUP.md's step 1 says, because it would break the build. Recommend updating SETUP.md to say Node 20. Want me to make that fix too?"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1275,"cache_read_input_tokens":21041,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1275},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5e55af6f-702d-4ccf-a4